---
title: Sweet Chili-Lime Glazed Pork Chops with Sweet Potato-Carrot Jumble, Sesame Seeds & Lime
description: Sweet Thai chili sauce, sweet soy glaze, and hoisin team up for a spicy-sweet-umami triple threat atop these juicy pan-seared pork chops. On the side is a colorful caramelized jumble of roasted sweet potatoes, red onion, and carrots showered with nutty sesame seeds for crunchy contrast. Before serving, a sprinkle of fresh scallions and squeeze of lime juice tops off this boldly seasoned, veggie-forward meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/65131f603cb5229806dac614-8eb01afe.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65131f603cb5229806dac614.pdf
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: East Asia
nutrition:
  calories: 680 kcal
  fat: 23 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 90 g
  sugar: 45 g
  protein: 33 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 1500 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-chili-lime-glazed-pork-chops-65131f603cb5229806dac614
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch pieces. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%oz} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into 1-inch-thick wedges.

Toss sweet potatoes, carrots, and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%tsp}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, divide between two sheets; roast on top and middle racks, swapping rack positions halfway through.) Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Quarter @lime{1}.

Pat @pork chops{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} and cover with #foil{} to keep warm. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in same pan over medium-low heat. Add scallion whites; cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant and tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz}, 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings), @sweet soy glaze{2 1/2%tbsp} (5 TBSP for 4), and juice from half the lime. (Be sure to measure the sweet soy glaze—we sent more!) Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce has slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide pork and sweet potato–carrot jumble between plates in separate sections. Spoon sauce over pork. Garnish sweet potato–carrot jumble with @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}. Garnish everything with scallion greens and serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.